description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 6 MONTHS TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for two six month secondments within the Manual Handling Department of the Health, Safety and Fire Team .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts are to assist with the training of new starters in response to the current pandemic. The successful candidates will be assisting our Manual Handling Trainers in delivering the All Wales Manual Handling Passport to meet the requirements of the Manual Handling Operations Regulations 1992.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience as a Patient Handling Workplace Assessor would be beneficial however all applications from existing Ward/Departmental staff who apply patient handling skills, during the course of their current role will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is across all sites and candidates may need to travel to different locations throughout Cwm Taf Morgannwg University Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ensure you discuss with your Line Manager prior to applying as you will need to be released from your current role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Darren Gill Corporate Manual Handling Advisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Darren.gill@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01443 443193&lt;/p&gt;
